<section class="faq-sec section-padding border-section faq-custom-scope">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="grid-faq-tops">
            <div class="faq-holdersmain">
                <h4 class="fs-60">Frequently Asked Questions</h4>
                <div>
                    <p>
                        Find answers to the most common questions about our
                        services. If you still need help, feel free to reach out
                        we’re here for you.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-container">
            <div class="faq-holders">
                <div class="number-dats">
                    <p class="faq-no">01</p>
                </div>
                <div class="alladat-hersss">
                    <div class="grid-faq">
                        <div class="title-faq">
                            <h6 class="faq-title">
                                Do I really need an app, or is a website enough?
                            </h6>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-icon">
                            <span class="faq-symbol"></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bootm-data">
                        <div class="faqy-deschere">
                            <p>
                                A website and an app do different jobs. A
                                website is for visitors who don't know you yet.
                                An app is for the customers who already do, and
                                who you want to come back. If your business
                                depends on repeat visits, bookings, or a direct
                                relationship with your customers, an app pays
                                for itself. If you mostly need to be found in
                                Google search results, a website might be
                                enough. We'll tell you honestly which one you
                                need on the first call.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-holders">
                <div class="number-dats">
                    <p class="faq-no">02</p>
                </div>
                <div class="alladat-hersss">
                    <div class="grid-faq">
                        <div class="title-faq">
                            <h6 class="faq-title">
                                How much does an app cost?
                            </h6>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-icon">
                            <span class="faq-symbol"></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bootm-data">
                        <div class="faqy-deschere">
                            <p>
                                It depends on what the app does. A focused MVP
                                for a startup typically lands between $20,000
                                and $60,000. A full production app for an
                                established business is usually $60,000 to
                                $150,000. Apps with complex backends, multiple
                                user roles, or heavy AI features can go higher.
                                We give you a written, fixed-scope quote before
                                any work starts — not estimates that creep
                                upward.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-holders">
                <div class="number-dats">
                    <p class="faq-no">03</p>
                </div>
                <div class="alladat-hersss">
                    <div class="grid-faq">
                        <div class="title-faq">
                            <h6 class="faq-title">How long does it take?</h6>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-icon">
                            <span class="faq-symbol"></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bootm-data">
                        <div class="faqy-deschere">
                            <p>
                                A simple app: 8 to 12 weeks. A medium-complexity
                                app: 3 to 6 months. A complex platform: 6 to 12
                                months. We'll give you a realistic timeline on
                                the discovery call.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-holders">
                <div class="number-dats">
                    <p class="faq-no">04</p>
                </div>
                <div class="alladat-hersss">
                    <div class="grid-faq">
                        <div class="title-faq">
                            <h6 class="faq-title">
                                Do I need iOS, Android, or both?
                            </h6>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-icon">
                            <span class="faq-symbol"></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bootm-data">
                        <div class="faqy-deschere">
                            <p>
                                Most of our clients launch on both.
                                Cross-platform tools like React Native and
                                Flutter let us build one codebase that runs on
                                both stores, which keeps cost reasonable. If
                                your customers are mostly on iPhones (US-based,
                                premium audiences) or mostly on Android (global,
                                value-conscious audiences), starting with one is
                                a smart way to validate before expanding.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="loadmore-button">
            <div class="universal-anchor">
                <a href="#" class="link-button">Load more</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <script>
            document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
                const container = document.querySelector(".faq-container");

                if (!container) return;

                let activeHeader = null;
                let activeContent = null;

                container.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
                    const header = e.target.closest(".grid-faq");
                    if (!header) return;

                    const faqHolder = header.closest(".faq-holders");
                    const bottomData = faqHolder.querySelector(".bootm-data");

                    const isSame = header === activeHeader;

                    // Remove previous active
                    if (activeHeader) activeHeader.classList.remove("active");
                    if (activeContent) activeContent.classList.remove("active");

                    // Toggle logic
                    if (!isSame) {
                        header.classList.add("active");
                        bottomData.classList.add("active");

                        activeHeader = header;
                        activeContent = bottomData;
                    } else {
                        activeHeader = null;
                        activeContent = null;
                    }
                });
            });
        </script>
    </div>
</section>
